TITLE: Storing GeoPoint in Firestore with React Native
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to store a GeoPoint value in a Firestore document. It updates the 'info.address.location' field of the 'users/ABC' document with a new GeoPoint instance, providing the latitude and longitude. GeoPoints are used to represent geographic locations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/firestore/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
firestore()
  .doc('users/ABC')
  .update({
    'info.address.location': new firestore.GeoPoint(53.483959, -2.244644),
  });
```

