TITLE: Implementing OpenID Connect Authentication with Azure AD in React Native Firebase
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to authenticate users using OpenID Connect with Azure AD as the provider. Uses react-native-app-auth for OAuth token retrieval and react-native-firebase for authentication. Requires proper configuration of Azure AD and Firebase console setup.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/auth/oidc-auth.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';
import { authorize } from 'react-native-app-auth';

// using react-native-app-auth to get oauth token from Azure AD
const config = {
  issuer: 'https://login.microsoftonline.com/XXX/v2.0',
  clientId: 'XXXX',
  redirectUrl: 'msauth.your.bundle.id://auth/',
  scopes: ['openid', 'profile', 'email', 'offline_access'],
  useNonce: false,
};

// Log in to get an authentication token
const authState = await authorize(config);

const credential = auth.OIDCAuthProvider.credential(
  'azure_test', // this is the "Provider ID" value from the firebase console
  authState.idToken,
);

await auth().signInWithCredential(credential);
```

