TITLE: Generating Text Stream with VertexAI
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to generate a text stream from the Vertex AI Gemini API, allowing for a response to be processed in chunks. It initializes Vertex AI, retrieves a generative model, and uses `generateContentStream()` to send a text prompt and then asynchronously iterates over the response stream to build and log the full text.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/vertexai/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import React from 'react';
import { AppRegistry, Button, Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { getApp } from '@react-native-firebase/app';
import { getVertexAI, getGenerativeModel } from '@react-native-firebase/vertexai';

function App() {
  return (
    <View>
      <Button
        title="generate content stream"
        onPress={async () => {
          const app = getApp();
          const vertexai = getVertexAI(app);
          const model = getGenerativeModel(vertexai, { model: 'gemini-1.5-flash' });

          const result = await model.generateContentStream('Write a short poem');

          let text = '';
          for await (const chunk of result.stream) {
            const chunkText = chunk.text();
            text += chunkText;
          }

          console.log(text);
        }}
      />
    </View>
  );
}
```

