TITLE: Email/Password Sign-In with Firebase
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to create and sign in a user using email and password with Firebase Authentication. It uses createUserWithEmailAndPassword method and handles errors like email already in use or invalid. Dependencies include @react-native-firebase/auth module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/auth/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';

auth()
  .createUserWithEmailAndPassword('jane.doe@example.com', 'SuperSecretPassword!')
  .then(() => {
    console.log('User account created & signed in!');
  })
  .catch(error => {
    if (error.code === 'auth/email-already-in-use') {
      console.log('That email address is already in use!');
    }

    if (error.code === 'auth/invalid-email') {
      console.log('That email address is invalid!');
    }

    console.error(error);
  });
```

