TITLE: Running a Firestore Transaction in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to execute a Firestore transaction using the `runTransaction` method. It atomically increments the 'likes' field on a 'Posts' collection document. Transactions ensure that writes occur with the latest server-side information, retrying if concurrent edits occur.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/firestore/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import firestore from '@react-native-firebase/firestore';

function onPostLike(postId) {
  // Create a reference to the post
  const postReference = firestore().doc(`posts/${postId}`);

  return firestore().runTransaction(async transaction => {
    // Get post data first
    const postSnapshot = await transaction.get(postReference);

    if (!postSnapshot.exists) {
      throw 'Post does not exist!';
    }

    transaction.update(postReference, {
      likes: postSnapshot.data().likes + 1,
    });
  });
}

onPostLike('ABC')
  .then(() => console.log('Post likes incremented via a transaction'))
  .catch(error => console.error(error));
```

