TITLE: Performing a Firestore Batch Write in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to perform a batch write operation in Firestore to delete all documents in a collection. It retrieves all users from the 'Users' collection, creates a batch instance, adds a delete operation for each user, and then commits the batch. Batch writes execute atomically and can contain any combination of `set`, `update`, or `delete` operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/firestore/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import firestore from '@react-native-firebase/firestore';

async function massDeleteUsers() {
  // Get all users
  const usersQuerySnapshot = await firestore().collection('Users').get();

  // Create a new batch instance
  const batch = firestore().batch();

  usersQuerySnapshot.forEach(documentSnapshot => {
    batch.delete(documentSnapshot.ref);
  });

  return batch.commit();
}

massDeleteUsers().then(() => console.log('All users deleted in a single batch operation.'));
```

