TITLE: Updating Nested Firestore Document Fields in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to update deeply nested values within a Firestore document using dot notation.  It updates the 'zipcode' field within the 'info.address' object of the document with ID 'ABC' in the 'Users' collection.  Dot notation provides a convenient way to modify specific nested properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/firestore/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import firestore from '@react-native-firebase/firestore';

firestore()
  .collection('Users')
  .doc('ABC')
  .update({
    'info.address.zipcode': 94040,
  })
  .then(() => {
    console.log('User updated!');
  });
```

