TITLE: Revoking Apple Sign-In Token with React Native Firebase
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to revoke an Apple Sign-In token using the `react-native-apple-authentication` and `@react-native-firebase/auth` libraries. It performs a refresh request to get an authorization code, and then revokes the token.  It requires the `react-native-apple-authentication` and `@react-native-firebase/auth` libraries to be installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/auth/social-auth.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';
import { appleAuth } from '@invertase/react-native-apple-authentication';

async function revokeSignInWithAppleToken() {
  // Get an authorizationCode from Apple
  const { authorizationCode } = await appleAuth.performRequest({
    requestedOperation: appleAuth.Operation.REFRESH,
  });

  // Ensure Apple returned an authorizationCode
  if (!authorizationCode) {
    throw new Error('Apple Revocation failed - no authorizationCode returned');
  }

  // Revoke the token
  return auth().revokeToken(authorizationCode);
}
```

