TITLE: Apple Sign-In Implementation with React Native Firebase
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to implement the Apple Sign-In flow using the `react-native-apple-authentication` and `@react-native-firebase/auth` libraries. It performs a sign-in request, retrieves the identity token and nonce, creates a Firebase credential, and signs the user in. It requires the `react-native-apple-authentication` and `@react-native-firebase/auth` libraries to be installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/auth/social-auth.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';
import { appleAuth } from '@invertase/react-native-apple-authentication';

async function onAppleButtonPress() {
  // Start the sign-in request
  const appleAuthRequestResponse = await appleAuth.performRequest({
    requestedOperation: appleAuth.Operation.LOGIN,
    // As per the FAQ of react-native-apple-authentication, the name should come first in the following array.
    // See: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-apple-authentication#faqs
    requestedScopes: [appleAuth.Scope.FULL_NAME, appleAuth.Scope.EMAIL],
  });

  // Ensure Apple returned a user identityToken
  if (!appleAuthRequestResponse.identityToken) {
    throw new Error('Apple Sign-In failed - no identify token returned');
  }

  // Create a Firebase credential from the response
  const { identityToken, nonce } = appleAuthRequestResponse;
  const appleCredential = auth.AppleAuthProvider.credential(identityToken, nonce);

  // Sign the user in with the credential
  return auth().signInWithCredential(appleCredential);
}
```

