TITLE: Handling Exceptions in Objective-C with Firebase Crashlytics
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to handle exceptions in an iOS application using React Native Firebase Crashlytics. It captures details of the exception and creates an NSError object with relevant information before recording it using 'RNFBCrashlyticsNativeHelper'. This requires the React Native Firebase Crashlytics library in the iOS project setup.
