TITLE: Detecting Background or Quit State Dynamic Link Events in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to detect if an application, when opened from a quit or background state, was launched via a dynamic link using the getInitialLink method. It requires the @react-native-firebase/dynamic-links package. The code examines the initial link and sets the initial route according to the link URL, making use of the React useEffect hook for asynchronous operation handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/dynamic-links/usage/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import dynamicLinks from '@react-native-firebase/dynamic-links';

function App() {
  useEffect(() => {
    dynamicLinks()
      .getInitialLink()
      .then(link => {
        if (link.url === 'https://invertase.io/offer') {
          // ...set initial route as offers screen
        }
      });
  }, []);

  return null;
}
```

