TITLE: Overriding Android SDK Versions in build.gradle
DESCRIPTION: Allows setting custom SDK versions in an Android build.gradle file for a React Native project. This might be necessary to avoid conflicts with other libraries, but it is not recommended as it can lead to future incompatibilities.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: groovy
CODE:
```
project.ext {
  set('react-native', [
    versions: [
      // Overriding Build/Android SDK Versions
      android : [
        minSdk    : 21, // 23+ if using auth module
        targetSdk : 33,
        compileSdk: 34,
      ],

      // Overriding Library SDK Versions
      firebase: [
        // Override Firebase SDK Version
        bom           : "33.12.0"
      ],
    ],
  ])
}
```

