TITLE: Migrating to Modular API: Firestore Namespaced Query
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to perform a Firestore query using the old namespaced API. It retrieves documents from the 'cities' collection where the capital field is true. This form is deprecated and should be replaced during migration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/react-native-firebase/blob/main/docs/migrating-to-v22.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import firestore from '@react-native-firebase/firestore';

const db = firestore();

const querySnapshot = await db.collection('cities').where('capital', '==', true).get();

querySnapshot.forEach(doc => {
  console.log(doc.id, ' => ', doc.data());
});
```

